From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yocto Builder <builder@yoctoproject.org>
Date: Tue, 7 Jan 2026 15:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] pci-host-generic: Add support for nvidia,tegra264-pcie

Thor (Tegra264) uses SBSA/ECAM PCIe controllers with DesignWare IP.
The controllers have memory regions (xal, xtl, xpl, ecam) compatible
with the DesignWare ECAM driver.

Add nvidia,tegra264-pcie to use the pci_dw_ecam_bus_ops,  same as
other DesignWare ECAM controllers like Synquacer and Armada.

Signed-off-by: Yocto Builder <builder@yoctoproject.org>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/pci-host-generic.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/pci-host-generic.c b/drivers/pci/controller/pci-host-generic.c
index 1234567890ab..1234567890ab 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pci-host-generic.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pci-host-generic.c
@@ -75,6 +75,9 @@ static const struct of_device_id gen_pci_of_match[] = {
 	{ .compatible = "snps,dw-pcie-ecam",
 	  .data = &pci_dw_ecam_bus_ops },

+	{ .compatible = "nvidia,tegra264-pcie",
+	  .data = &pci_dw_ecam_bus_ops },
+
 	{ },
 };

--
